name: pytest-openfiles
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pytest-openfiles" %}
{% set version = "0.5.0" %}
{% set git_url = "https://github.com/astropy/pytest-openfiles" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 179c2911d8aee3441fee051aba08e0d9b4dab61b829ae4811906d5c49a3b0a58

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
    - setuptools_scm
    - pytest >=4.6
    - psutil
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - pytest >=4.6
    - psutil

test:
  imports:
    - pytest_openfiles

about:
  home: {{ git_url }}
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.rst
  summary: Pytest plugin for detecting inadvertent open file handles
  description: |
    This package provides a plugin for the pytest framework that allows
    developers to detect whether any file handles or other file-like objects
    were inadvertently left open at the end of a unit test.
  doc_url: {{ git_url }}
  dev_url: {{ git_url }}

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - astrofrog-conda-forge
    - drdavella
    - mwcraig
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
